  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Safe Drinking Water and Improved Sanitation and Hygiene Practices for Vulnerable IDPs and Host Commu</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved sanitation and hygiene practices in affected communities reduce the spread of diarrheal diseases.
Increased Access to safe drinking water in order to reduce on cases of cholera outbreak within the targeted community.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The first objective of this project aims to provide safe water access, which will be achieved through repairs of dysfunctional water points. Where people do not have a safe source of water, buckets, aluminium sulphate and aqua tabs will be provided to ensure the safe treatment of water at household level.
The second objective will ensure good hygiene practices and safe faecal disposal. This will be carried out through mass campaigns for communities and dissemination of messages on good hygiene practices and improved sanitation at household level. The above will be carried out by trained community hygiene promoters. Youth will be involved in supporting this process. The IA &#x2013; HPP 2016 is currently implementing latrines and there will be latrines built in locations.  Safe sanitation mechanisms will be developed with communities using the sanitation ladder and this includes burying both adult and children&#x2019;s faces to avoid water contamination</narrative>
  </description>
